5. What are Weights?

Weights tell the importance of every feature.

Higher weight = More influence.

Example

Area Weight = 0.9
Age Weight = 0.1

Area affects prediction more.

6. What is Bias?

Bias shifts the activation function.

Formula

z = wx+b

Without bias, the model becomes less flexible.

7. Why is bias important?

