54. What is Adam?

Adaptive Moment Estimation.

Combines Momentum + RMSprop.

55. Advantages of Adam?
Fast convergence
Adaptive learning rates
Works well on sparse gradients
56. What is RMSprop?

Uses moving average of squared gradients.

57. What is Momentum?

Accelerates optimization and reduces oscillations.

58. What is Learning Rate?

Controls step size.

59. Large learning rate?

Overshoots minimum.

60. Small learning rate?

Very slow convergence.

